          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the batter",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 180°C conventional (160°C fan). Grease and line two 20 cm round tins. Melt the chocolate and butter together in a heatproof bowl set over barely simmering water, stirring occasionally. Remove from the heat and stir in the sugar. Beat in the eggs one at a time. Fold in the almond flour, rice flour, cocoa powder, baking powder, and vanilla extract until just combined.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Divide the batter evenly between the tins and smooth the surfaces. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes until a skewer inserted in the centre comes out with no wet batter. Cool completely in the tins before turning out.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the ganache and assemble",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the cream until just simmering. Pour over the chopped chocolate in a heatproof bowl and leave for 2 minutes, then stir until smooth. Allow to cool at room temperature until thick enough to spread (about 30 minutes, or 15 minutes in the refrigerator). Spread half the ganache over one cooled sponge layer, place the second layer on top, and spread the remaining ganache over the top and sides.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
